        "title": "Fat Embolism and Trauma Complications — Core Principles",
        "definition": "Systemic complications of major orthopaedic trauma including fat embolism syndrome, ARDS, and systemic inflammatory response.",
        "summary": "Fat embolism presents with hypoxia, neurologic changes, and petechiae after long-bone fractures. Early stabilization and supportive care are mainstays."
